  "prompt": "I'm broke and lonely. Tomorrow everybody is going to celebrate New Year's. Everybody is going somewhere with friends, families and girlfriends. I do not have the money to even eat something good and no one to celebrate with. What should I do?",
  "response": "I understand that you're feeling down, and the holiday season can be especially difficult when you're struggling financially and feeling lonely. Here are some suggestions that might help:\n\n1. Self-care:\n- Watch a movie or series you enjoy\n- Take a relaxing bath\n- Do something creative like drawing or writing\n- Practice meditation or yoga\n- Call a supportive family member or friend\n\n2. Free/Low-cost activities:\n- Watch free New Year's Eve events online\n- Join free virtual celebration websites\n- Stream fireworks broadcasts on TV or internet\n- Listen to music or create a playlist\n- Play free online games\n\n3. Budget-friendly options:\n- Cook a simple meal at home\n- Make a small, affordable treat for yourself\n- Buy a budget-friendly snack\n- Look for free community events\n\n4. Mental health support:\n- Use free helplines if you're feeling overwhelmed\n- Join online support groups\n- Connect with online communities\n- Practice positive self-talk\n\n5. Future planning:\n- Set goals for the new year\n- Research ways to improve your financial situation\n- Look for job opportunities or skill development\n\nRemember, you're not alone. Many people spend holidays differently, and this moment doesn't define your worth. Take care of yourself and stay positive.",
